// @test: run
// @level: L0
// @tier: 2
// @tags: codegen, aot, mount-core, libc-allowlist, side-effects
// @expected-stdout: hi
// @expected-exit: 0
// @description: AOT mount-core println side-effect visibility regression.
//
// 2026-04-26 #106: `println("hi")` under `mount core.*` produced no
// observable output despite normal exit. Root cause: the Phase 3.6
// bodyless-decl safety net in `crates/verum_codegen/src/llvm/vbc_lowering.rs`
// was stubbing libc symbols absent from `is_libc_extern`. LLVM
// optimization patterns sometimes lower trailing-newline writes to
// `puts(s)`, but `puts` was missing from the allow-list. The stub
// `mov w0, #0; ret` masquerades as "0 chars written, success" — the
// caller sees Ok(0) and discards the result, output is silently
// dropped.
//
// Fix (1d3f89f0) — added puts/putchar/perror/putc/getc/getchar to
// `is_libc_extern`. These remain undefined LLVM declarations so dyld
// resolves them to the real libc implementations at link/load time.
//
// This test pins the contract: side effects of println must surface
// to stdout in AOT mount-core programs.

mount core.*;
mount core.io.stdio.{println};

fn main() -> Int {
    println("hi");
    0
}
